    "narrative": "The heart of our lineup today is anchored by **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts an elite 80.92 score against Aaron Civale. His matchup benefits from a significant park factor boost and a favorable SP skill rating, solidifying his role as our primary offensive engine. We also see high-ceiling potential from **Will Smith** (68.56), **Bryson Stott** (66.60), and **Tyler Freeman** (64.84). **Taylor Ward** is a high-upside play at 64.43; while facing the tough Max Fried, he benefits significantly from his leadoff spot and a 5% wind-out advantage, which offsets the pitcher's skill. **Cal Raleigh** (63.57) and **Geraldo Perdomo** (63.30) provide strong depth, with **Geraldo Perdomo** specifically bolstered by a 10% wind-out factor that makes him a surprisingly efficient play against the lefty Matthew Boyd.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was leaving **Masyn Winn** (45.07) out of the starting nine. While his sprint speed provides the SB potential we prioritize, the unfavorable matchup against a 3.59 xERA arm combined with the optimizer's preference for high-OBP bats like **Jonathan Aranda** (65.36) squeezed him out. **Jonathan Aranda** remains a key start, capitalizing on a 12% platoon edge against Tyler Mahle. We are proceeding with caution regarding **Wenceel Perez** (47.22); despite his 8th-order slot, his slow-delivery matchup against Jack Leiter keeps his score above our 40-point floor, but he is the first candidate to be replaced if late-breaking lineup news confirms a defensive substitution. All projections remain contingent on the \"Lineup Pending\" status; if **Will Smith** or **Gleyber Torres** drop in the order, their efficiency scores will require immediate re-evaluation.",
